        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 4:12PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 412 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Mocksville, or near Harmony, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mocksville, Harmony, Sheffield, Turnersburg, and Cool Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
